== Tomato Onion Jam ==

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1} and mince a
few slices until you have 2 TBSP. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Finely chop
@chives{1/4%oz}. Place @tricolor peppercorns{1%tbsp} in a #zip-close bag{} and
pound using a #mallet{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{} until coarsely ground. Heat
1 TBSP @butter{3%tbsp} and a drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over
medium heat.

Add sliced onion, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} to pan.
Cook, tossing occasionally, until soft and browned, about ~{10%minutes}. Increase
heat to medium high. Stir in tomatoes, @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, and ⅓ cup
water. Simmer until jammy, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer
to a #small bowl{} and cover. Wipe out pan.

== Risotto ==

Meanwhile, pour 3 cups water into a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave on
high until warm, about ~{1%minute}. Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in another
large pan over medium heat. Add minced onion and cook, tossing, until just
softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @Arborio rice{3/4%cup} and a few big pinches
of salt; cook until translucent, about ~{1%minute}.

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{2} and ⅓ cup warm water into pan with rice. Simmer,
stirring, until liquid is mostly absorbed. Add more warm water to pan ⅓ cup at a
time, allowing rice to absorb most of the water before adding more and stirring
after each addition. Continue until rice is al dente, about ~{25%minutes}
(you may not use all of the water). Season with salt and pepper.

== Steaks ==

Around the time that rice has cooked 10 minutes, pat @rib-eye steak{20%oz} dry with
a #paper towel{}. Season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of olive
oil in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Add steaks and cook to desired
doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Remove risotto from heat and stir in @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, 2 TBSP butter, and
1 tsp peppercorns (use more to taste). Season with salt.

Once steaks have rested ~{5%minutes}, slice against the grain. Divide steaks and
risotto between plates. Garnish with chives. Top steak with onion jam,
reheating jam in #microwave{} first if necessary. Season with remaining
peppercorns, if desired.

> TIP: If risotto is stiff, stir in up to ¼ cup water to loosen.